ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[African horse sickness (AHS) is an infectious but noncontagious viral
disease affecting all species of equidae caused by an orbivirus of the
family Reoviridae and characterised by alterations in respiratory and
circulatory functions. AHS is transmitted by at least 2 species of
Culicoides. 9 different serotypes have been described. All serotypes of AHS
occur in eastern and southern Africa.
The South African Immunization schedule, including African Horse Sickness,
can be seen at <http://www.obpvaccines.co.za/immunization.htm>.
The package insert of the AHS vaccine is available at:
<http://www.obpvaccines.co.za/inserts/english/horsesickness.pdf>
Data on the African Horse Sickness (AHS) serotype involved in the current
cases will be appreciated. AHS does not affect humans. - Mod.AS]
